From 5fcedf42c4eb4a3861196c002aff5f02b5b8871b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?K=C3=A9vin=20Remondi=C3=A8re?= <remondiere@openclaw.local>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 2026 23:15:36 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] fix: MTP decode working for Qwen3.5-35B-A3B MoE (bug
 #7+#8)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Bug #7: compute buffer reserve for MTP graph — added graph_reserve
with MTP_OP_WARMUP at init to pre-allocate for larger MTP graph.

Bug #8: llama_set_inputs SEGV on GDN inputs — MTP graph has no
recurrent/GDN layers, skip inp_s_mask/inp_s_seq/inp_s_seq_qnext
when mtp_op_type != MTP_OP_NONE.

Total: 8 bugs found and fixed for MTP on QWEN35MOE:
1. TENSOR_SKIP unconditional
2. cparams.mtp whitelist (GLM4_MOE only)
3. Gated Q (wq = Q+Gate) in build_mtp_tail
4. M-RoPE is_multi flag
5. Compute buffer not reserved for MTP graph
6. llama_set_inputs crash on GDN inputs
7-8. Combined in this commit

Result: MTP decode produces logits, server generates text with
speculative MTP drafting. First MTP working on Qwen3.5-35B-A3B MoE.
Acceptance rate = 0% (expected: MTP weights are F16, not quantized
like main model IQ3_S — need quantization alignment).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/llama.cpp | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/llama.cpp b/src/llama.cpp
index 9c2f74b..2a7aa75 100644
--- a/src/llama.cpp
+++ b/src/llama.cpp
@@ -3038,7 +3038,7 @@ static void llama_set_inputs(llama_context & lctx, const llama_batch & batch) {
         }
     }
 
-    if (kv_self.recurrent) {
+    if (kv_self.recurrent && cparams.mtp_op_type == MTP_OP_NONE) {
         const int64_t n_kv = kv_self.n;
 
         if (lctx.inp_s_mask) {
@@ -3085,7 +3085,7 @@ static void llama_set_inputs(llama_context & lctx, const llama_batch & batch) {
         }
     }
 
-    if (lctx.inp_s_seq_qnext) {
+    if (lctx.inp_s_seq_qnext && cparams.mtp_op_type == MTP_OP_NONE) {
         const int64_t n_tokens = batch.n_tokens;
 
         GGML_ASSERT(ggml_backend_buffer_is_host(lctx.inp_s_seq_qnext->buffer));
